%% OSPP Session Lifecycle State Machine
%% Reference: spec/05-state-machines.md, Section 2

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Pending : Session initiated<br/>(user requests session)

    Pending --> Authorized : Payment/credits verified
    Pending --> Failed : Payment declined<br/>Insufficient funds

    Authorized --> Active : StartService accepted<br/>by station
    Authorized --> Failed : StartService rejected<br/>or timeout (10s)

    Active --> Stopping : StopService requested<br/>(user, server, or timer)
    Active --> Failed : Hardware fault<br/>Connection lost (after grace period)

    Stopping --> Completed : Station confirms stop<br/>Final MeterValues received
    Stopping --> Failed : Stop timeout (10s)<br/>Station unresponsive

    Completed --> [*]
    Failed --> [*]

    state Pending {
        [*] --> VerifyingPayment
        VerifyingPayment --> CreditCheck : Wallet payment
        VerifyingPayment --> CardCapture : Card payment
    }

    state Active {
        [*] --> Dispensing
        Dispensing --> Dispensing : MeterValues<br/>(every MeterValuesInterval (default 15s))
    }

    note right of Pending
        Timeout: 10s
        No service delivered yet
    end note

    note right of Active
        MeterValues reported periodically
        Max duration: configurable (default 600s)
        Implementation detail: actual substates
        (VerifyingPayment, CreditCheck, CardCapture,
        Dispensing) vary by station type and payment
        processor. These are illustrative, not normative.
    end note

    note right of Completed
        Receipt generated
        Wallet debited for actual usage
        Unused credits refunded
    end note

    note right of Failed
        Refund initiated if payment was captured
        Partial refund based on last MeterValues
    end note
